@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000/api

### 1. Register a Student
# @name registerStudent
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Test Student",
  "email": "student@test.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "role": "STUDENT"
}

###

### 2. Login as Student (Sets HttpOnly Cookie)
# @name loginStudent
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "student@test.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

###

### 3. Verify Authentication (Get Me)
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me

###

### 4. Fetch Subjects (To get a subjectId for posting a doubt)
# @name getSubjects
GET {{baseUrl}}/subjects

###

### 5. Post a Doubt (Requires you to copy a subjectId and chapterId from the previous request)
POST {{baseUrl}}/doubts
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "How does Quantum Entanglement work?",
  "description": "I am struggling to understand the concept of entanglement in the Classical Mechanics chapter. Can someone explain?",
  "subjectId": "REPLACE_WITH_SUBJECT_ID",
  "chapterId": "REPLACE_WITH_CHAPTER_ID"
}

###

### 6. Get Doubt Feed
GET {{baseUrl}}/doubts

###

### 7. Register a Faculty Member
# @name registerFaculty
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Dr. Smith",
  "email": "faculty@test.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "role": "FACULTY"
}

###

### 8. Login as Faculty (Overrides previous cookie)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "faculty@test.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

###

### 9. Post an Answer (Requires you to copy a doubtId from step 6)
POST {{baseUrl}}/doubts/REPLACE_WITH_DOUBT_ID/answers
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "content": "Quantum entanglement occurs when a group of particles are generated, interact, or share spatial proximity in a way such that the quantum state of each particle of the group cannot be described independently of the state of the others."
}

###

### 10. Admin Analytics (Requires Admin Login)
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/analytics

###

### 11. Logout
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/logout
